"""
Mavrovouniotis et al. (2020) E-CVRP benchmark set converted into a single
Python file in a "customer_data.py-like" structure for GASA-style solvers.

Source repo:
  https://github.com/Mavrovouniotis/e-cvrp_benchmark_instances

Each instance is stored in INSTANCES[name] with keys:
  - num_customers
  - locations: list[(x, y)] with depot first, then customers, then stations
  - demand: aligned with locations; stations have 0 demand
  - depot: always 0 (index in locations)
  - vehicle_capacity, battery_capacity, vehicles
  - original_node_ids: mapping back to original node IDs in the .evrp file

Usage:
  from mavrovouniotis_ecvrp_instances_for_gasa import get_instance
  inst = get_instance("E-n29-k4-s7")
"""
